By Joe Wright
News Editor

One more remnant of the J. Dennis
O’Connor administration is gone, follow-
ing an announcement yesterday that
Senior Vice Chancellor for Business and
Finance Ben Tuchi is resigning that post,
effective immediately.

With the resignation, Tuchi becomes
one more in a long line of Pitt administra-
tors to leave since O’Connor announced
his own resignation on April 10, 1995.

Interim Chancellor Mark Nordenberg

accepted Tuchi’s resignation, thanking
him for his efforts on behalf of the uni-
versity. ! .

“Shortly after arriving. on the Pitt cam-
pus, Dr. Tuchi pledged that he would
work tirelessly to make our business and
finance unit one of the best in American
higher education,” Nordenberg said in a
written statement. “He has honored that
pledge through his efforts, and achieving
that level of quality will remain our
goal.”

But Tuchi’s resignation has also
sparked a shake—up in the Office of
Business and Finance. Assistant Interim
Chancellor Jerry Cochran will serve as
interim vice chancellor for business,
while Associate Vice Chancellor for
Budget and Administration Arthur
Ramicone will serve as interim vice
chancellor for finance.

“The uncoupling of business and
finance, at least for the short term, is

deliberate,” Nordenberg said. “That sepa-
ration should facilitate a study of both
structure and staffing in these areas,
which will be undertaken in the weeks
ahead as part of a more general review of
the university organization.”

.Cochran’s responsibilities will be for
the business, computing and information
services, facilities management and
human resource functions. Ramicone will
have responsibility for budget and admin-
istration and the controller’s office.

“Anytime there’s a change like this, it
provides an opportunity to energize the
units involved,” Cochran said.

Tuchi said he will remain at Pitt as a
faculty member in the Katz School of
Business. .

Before joining Pitt, Tuchi served as
vice chancellor for business and finance
and chief financial officer for the
University of North Carolina at Chapel

